    <stitle>FULL POWER HYDRAULIC ABS BRAKE SYSTEM - SYSTEM MAINTENANCE - wheel speed sensor adjustment</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl04048402" graphiccount="1">
        <title>wheel speed sensor adjustment</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Sensor Adjustment</title>
            <para>On steering axles, the sensor is typically accessible on the in-board side of the steering knuckle. On
                drive axles, the sensor is typically accessible on the in-board side of the rear axle spindle. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404840">FIGURE 45</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>To adjust the sensor, push the sensor in until it contacts the tooth ring:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Do not pry or push sensors with sharp objects</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sensors will self-adjust during wheel rotation.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>No gap is allowable at installation. During normal operation a gap not to exceed 1.02 mm (0.04
                        inch) is allowable.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0404840" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g0404840" filename="../figg04/G0404813.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Typical Wheel Speed Sensor Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FRONT SENSOR BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRONT SENSOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. REAR SENSOR CABLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
